# Snyk policy file — https://docs.snyk.io/snyk-cli/test-for-vulnerabilities/the-.snyk-file
# Provenance: decisions, not just dates (see STANDARDS.md).
version: v1.25.0

# Snyk Code (SAST) exclusions.
exclude:
  code:
    # harness/score_answers.py is a LOCAL developer scoring tool, run by hand from
    # the repo root over answer-transcript files the developer themselves passes on
    # the command line. Snyk flags `argv -> open()` as Path Traversal (CWE-23), which
    # is intrinsic to any file-processing CLI. The code is nonetheless hardened: the
    # path is realpath-resolved and confined to the working-directory tree
    # (see _safe_path). There is no service boundary and no untrusted input, so this
    # is an accepted, reviewed false-positive — not a runtime vulnerability.
    - harness/score_answers.py
